Create a struct called Person using typedef with the following fields:
    char name[50];
    char surname[50];
    int age;
    float height;
    float weight;

Create a function called createPerson that takes Person pointer argument and a string argument.
string argument in the following format = Bruce,Wayne,24,1.78,84.0
Than you need to parse, split and assign the string to the Person struct.

You will use atoi function to convert string to int.
You will use atof function to convert string to float.

EXAMPLE:
    char numStr[] = "24";
    int num = atoi(numStr);

    char numStr[] = "1.78";
    float num = atof(numStr); 

void createPerson(Person *p, char *str) {
    // Fill your code here
}

Then create a function called printPerson that takes Person pointer argument.
This function will print the Person struct to screen.

-----------MAIN--------------
Person person;
createPerson(&person, "Bruce,Wayne,24,1.78,84.0");
printPerson(&person);
